#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.109"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.109:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.109:0.2"
msgid "11. Phāsuvihāravagga"
msgstr "11. Living Comfortably"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.109:0.3"
msgid "109. Cātuddisasutta"
msgstr "109. All Four Directions"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.109:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu cātuddiso hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities has all four directions covered."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.109:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"accomplished in appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing "
"danger in the slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.4"
msgid ""
"bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"comprehending them theoretically."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.5"
msgid ""
"santuṭṭho hoti "
"itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;"
msgstr ""
"They’re content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines "
"and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.6"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;"
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.7"
msgid ""
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.109:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi, kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu cātuddiso "
"hotī”ti."
msgstr "A mendicant with these five qualities has all four directions covered.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.109:1.9"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
